06, pp. 563-566; Guo, T., Diener, M.D., Chai, Y., Alford, M.J., Haufler, R.E., McClure, S.M., Uranium stabilization of C28: A tetravalent fullerene (1992) Science, 257, pp. 1661-1663; Guo, T., Smalley, R.E., Scuseria, G.E., Abinitio theoretical predictions of C28, C28H4, C28F4, (TiC28)H4, and MC28 (M=Mg, Al, Si, S, Ca, Sc, Ti, Ge, Zr, and Sn) (1993) Journal of Chemical Physics, 99, pp. 352-359; Hansen, J., Sato, M., Ruedy, R., Lacis, A., Oinas, V., Global warming in the twenty-first century: An alternative scenario (2000) Proceedings of the National Academy of Science of USA, 97, pp. 9875-9880; Haywood, J.M., Ramaswamy, V., Global sensitivity studies of the direct radiative forcing due to anthropogenic sulfate and black carbon aerosols (1998) Journal of Geophysical Research, 103, pp. 6043-6058; Jacobson, M.Z., Strong radiative heating due to the mixing state of black carbon in atmospheric aerosols (2001) Nature, 409, pp. 695-697; Katrinak, K.A., Rez, P., Buseck, P.R., Structural variations in individual carbonaceous particles from an urban aerosol (1992) Environmental Science and Technology, 26, pp. 1967-1976; Koshio, A., Inakuma, M., Sugai, T., Shinohara, H., A preparative scale synthesis of C36 by high-temperature laser-vaporization: Purification and identification of C36H6 and C36H6O (2000) Journal of the American Chemical Society, 122, pp. 398-399; Koshio, A., Inakuma, M., Zhong, W.W., Sugai, T., Shinohara, H., In situ laser-furnace TOF mass spectrometry of C36 and the large-scale production by arc-discharge (2000) Journal of Physical Chemistry B, 104, pp. 7908-7913; Kroto, H.W., The stability of the fullerenes Cn, with n=24, 28, 32, 36, 50, 60 and 70 (1987) Nature, 329, pp. 529-531; Lary, D.J., Lee, A.M., Toumi, R., Newchurch, M.J., Pirre, M., Renard, J.B., Carbon aerosols and atmospheric photochemistry (1997) Journal of Geophysical Research, 102, pp. 3671-3682; Lu, X., Chen, Z.F., Curved pi-conjugation, aromaticity, and the related chemistry of small fullerene